+<html>
+<body>
+Reports <code>if</code> statements inside loops which can contain <code>break</code> inside and semantics won't change.
+<p><b>Example:</b></p>
+<pre><code>
+  boolean found = false;
+  for (int i : arr) {
+    if (i > 10) {
+      found = true;
+    }
+  }
+</code></pre>
+<p>Can be replaced with:</p>
+<pre><code>
+  boolean found = false;
+  for (int i : arr) {
+    if (i > 10) {
+      found = true;
+      break;
+    }
+  }
+</code></pre>
+<!-- tooltip end -->
+</body>
+</html>
